2072.subject: LL
2072.descrlong: Develops competency in cross-cultural analysis, involving a working knowledge of one's own ethnic heritage and the ability to make constructive comparisons with at least one other ethnic group. Addresses a conceptual understanding of culture, methodologies for studying and understanding culture, knowledge of crosscultural relations in the U.S., sociocultural experiences of U.S.-based social/ethnic groups and other societies, power relations and equity, and socio-political systems and effects on "status" of a cultural group. (LL Core class)
